WEBVTT

00:01:37.759 --> 00:01:38.960
No, we have to go down.

00:01:45.880 --> 00:01:46.960
I can hold on.

00:01:48.800 --> 00:01:49.640
Stop it.

00:01:50.520 --> 00:01:52.650
Look at how strong the wind is outside.

00:01:53.039 --> 00:01:55.370
The signal equipment might malfunction.

00:01:55.400 --> 00:01:57.039
You need to keep a close eye on it.

00:01:57.039 --> 00:01:58.520
Hold on, my ass!

00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:01.890
Do you want to be buried in the martyrs' cemetery?

00:02:02.400 --> 00:02:05.840
That way, you'd have to come pay your respects to me every year.

00:02:05.840 --> 00:02:07.800
Pay my respects to you? Every year?

00:02:08.360 --> 00:02:09.440
If you die on a mission,

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:11.280
you'll likely be buried in Jiuquan.

00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:12.740
I don't have time for that.

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:14.400
When the time comes,

00:02:14.400 --> 00:02:16.120
I'll just use you as an excuse

00:02:16.240 --> 00:02:18.160
to get together with Bao and Nan.

00:02:18.160 --> 00:02:19.200
We'll have a good time.

00:02:19.200 --> 00:02:20.800
I won't have time to miss you.

00:02:21.120 --> 00:02:23.120
Acting tough and pushing yourself

00:02:23.120 --> 00:02:24.200
proves nothing.

00:02:24.640 --> 00:02:26.040
It only proves that you're an idiot.

00:02:26.040 --> 00:02:27.600
Okay, I'll sleep for a bit.

00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:29.600
Remember to monitor the equipment.

00:02:30.320 --> 00:02:31.520
Mobile TT&C Station 3

00:02:31.560 --> 00:02:32.620
calling Station 1.

00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:34.720
Mobile TT&C Station 3

00:02:34.720 --> 00:02:35.780
calling Station 1.

00:02:36.160 --> 00:02:36.960
Wait a moment.

00:02:37.840 --> 00:02:38.840
Xiu, it's for you.

00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:40.960
This is Station 1. Go ahead, Station 3.

00:02:40.960 --> 00:02:42.220
How is Ying Ziqi doing?

00:02:42.440 --> 00:02:43.970
His fever is getting worse.

00:02:44.079 --> 00:02:45.680
And the wind is stronger now.

00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:47.840
Can you send someone up here immediately?

00:02:47.840 --> 00:02:48.240
I know.

00:02:48.240 --> 00:02:49.400
The meteorology team has reported it,

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:51.280
and I've reported to the superiors as well.

00:02:51.280 --> 00:02:52.160
As soon as conditions permit,

00:02:52.160 --> 00:02:54.890
we will dispatch a vehicle up there immediately.

00:02:58.200 --> 00:02:58.930
Understood.

00:03:13.840 --> 00:03:15.040
The voltage is unstable.

00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:18.240
Don't let it affect the satellite communication signal.

00:04:34.760 --> 00:04:36.620
Return to your posts and stand by.

00:04:38.280 --> 00:04:39.210
What's going on?

00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:42.320
Orbital data parameters are abnormal.

00:04:42.320 --> 00:04:43.920
All posts, report your data.

00:04:46.240 --> 00:04:47.560
The satellite is still within monitoring range.

00:04:47.560 --> 00:04:48.600
Parameter anomalies detected.

00:04:48.600 --> 00:04:50.060
All posts, please report.

00:04:50.520 --> 00:04:52.450
Report. Telemetry signal is lost.

00:04:52.960 --> 00:04:54.000
What happened?

00:04:55.360 --> 00:04:57.360
Contact all mobile T&C posts

00:04:57.600 --> 00:05:00.060
to report satellite data and signal status.

00:05:01.880 --> 00:05:03.120
Mobile T&C, attention.

00:05:03.120 --> 00:05:04.240
This is Xi'an.

00:05:04.240 --> 00:05:05.840
Satellite orbital data is abnormal.

00:05:05.840 --> 00:05:06.840
Signal is lost.

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:09.040
All stations, please report telemetry information.

00:05:09.040 --> 00:05:11.000
Send real-time flight control data.

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:12.320
Mobile T&C 1 reporting.

00:05:12.320 --> 00:05:13.920
Uplink signal interrupted.

00:05:14.720 --> 00:05:16.400
Mobile Station 2 telemetry abnormal.

00:05:16.400 --> 00:05:17.360
Signal interrupted.

00:05:17.360 --> 00:05:17.840
Reporting.

00:05:17.840 --> 00:05:20.640
Signals from Station 1 and 2 are both interrupted.

00:05:28.120 --> 00:05:29.780
Stations 3 and 4 have signals.

00:05:30.960 --> 00:05:32.200
Mobile Station 3,

00:05:32.200 --> 00:05:34.060
please report data information.

00:05:37.480 --> 00:05:38.680
Mobile Station 3,

00:05:38.680 --> 00:05:39.680
this is Xi'an.

00:05:39.680 --> 00:05:41.159
Please report if normal.

00:05:42.320 --> 00:05:43.600
Mobile Station 3,

00:05:43.600 --> 00:05:45.460
please report data information.

00:06:06.360 --> 00:06:07.440
Mobile Telemetry Station 3,

00:06:07.440 --> 00:06:08.970
please report your status.

00:06:12.800 --> 00:06:13.880
Mobile Telemetry Station 3,

00:06:13.880 --> 00:06:15.410
please report your status.

00:06:17.520 --> 00:06:19.120
Mobile Telemetry Station 3.

00:06:23.920 --> 00:06:25.980
Calling Mobile Telemetry Station 3.

00:06:29.440 --> 00:06:30.560
Mobile Telemetry Station 3,

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:32.090
please respond if you copy.

00:06:39.760 --> 00:06:41.820
Calling Mobile Telemetry Station 3.

00:06:43.520 --> 00:06:44.560
Mobile Telemetry Station 3,

00:06:44.560 --> 00:06:46.090
please report your status.

00:07:29.200 --> 00:07:30.280
Mobile TT&C 3.

00:07:30.280 --> 00:07:31.360
This is Xi'an.

00:07:31.360 --> 00:07:33.560
Please report if everything is normal.

00:07:59.400 --> 00:08:01.360
Forget about Mobile TT&C 3 for now.

00:08:01.560 --> 00:08:03.200
Mobile TT&C 4, take over.

00:08:35.720 --> 00:08:38.380
Receive the satellite orbit data immediately.

00:08:38.799 --> 00:08:39.659
Number 4, copy.

00:08:57.720 --> 00:08:58.360
Exciting.

00:08:58.360 --> 00:08:59.620
That almost killed me.

00:09:02.320 --> 00:09:02.920
Wu Wei.

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:04.640
Wu Wei.

00:09:05.400 --> 00:09:06.120
Wu Wei.

00:09:08.040 --> 00:09:08.840
What's wrong?

00:09:11.520 --> 00:09:12.000
What's wrong?

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:12.920
Calling.

00:09:12.920 --> 00:09:13.920
Reply quickly.

00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:14.880
Hurry up.

00:09:15.320 --> 00:09:16.360
Hurry, hurry up.

00:09:18.880 --> 00:09:19.640
Mobile TT&C 3,

00:09:19.640 --> 00:09:20.300
reporting.

00:09:22.040 --> 00:09:23.080
Mobile Telemetry 3,

00:09:23.080 --> 00:09:24.040
this is Xi'an.

00:09:24.920 --> 00:09:26.050
Mobile Telemetry 3,

00:09:26.360 --> 00:09:28.160
why didn't you respond just now?

00:09:28.480 --> 00:09:30.320
There was a circuit issue, so I went to fix it.

00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:30.600
I didn't want it to affect anything.

00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:33.160
Why did you leave your post without reporting first?

00:09:33.160 --> 00:09:34.290
Report the data now.

00:09:34.600 --> 00:09:35.800
The telemetry signal is normal.

00:09:35.800 --> 00:09:37.640
Everything is normal. Please advise.

00:09:37.640 --> 00:09:38.700
The follow-up work

00:09:38.800 --> 00:09:41.060
will be taken over by Mobile Telemetry 4.

00:09:42.120 --> 00:09:42.760
Oh no.

00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:44.600
Attention, all stations.

00:09:44.600 --> 00:09:45.760
This is Xi'an.

00:09:46.160 --> 00:09:48.090
Please report the telemetry data.

00:09:51.200 --> 00:09:52.200
Mobile Tracking 1.

00:09:52.200 --> 00:09:54.080
Signal restored. Telemetry normal.

00:09:54.080 --> 00:09:55.720
Downlink signal is still fluctuating.

00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:56.780
Mobile Tracking 4.

00:09:56.960 --> 00:09:58.880
Telemetry normal. Orbit data normal.

00:09:58.880 --> 00:09:59.480
Report.

00:09:59.480 --> 00:10:01.120
Satellite attitude alert cleared.

00:10:01.120 --> 00:10:02.780
Attitude restored to normal.

00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:03.400
Nan.

00:10:04.800 --> 00:10:05.560
Wei and Qi.

00:10:05.560 --> 00:10:06.840
Did something happen to them?

00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:08.240
Leaving posts without permission.

00:10:08.240 --> 00:10:09.440
Is it very serious?

00:10:17.080 --> 00:10:18.740
Looks like we broke the rules.

00:10:20.400 --> 00:10:21.600
Missed the call.

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:24.930
Left our post without permission.

00:10:25.240 --> 00:10:26.880
If I didn't go for the emergency repairs,

00:10:26.880 --> 00:10:29.140
we couldn't have completed the mission.

00:10:29.520 --> 00:10:31.380
We should have reported it first.

00:10:34.120 --> 00:10:34.880
Forget it.

00:10:34.880 --> 00:10:36.410
Just take care of yourself.

00:10:40.240 --> 00:10:41.240
How are you doing?

00:10:44.520 --> 00:10:45.520
It's all my fault.

00:10:56.720 --> 00:10:57.400
Hello.

00:10:57.760 --> 00:10:59.360
How long until you get here?

00:11:00.680 --> 00:11:01.480
Five minutes.

00:11:02.040 --> 00:11:02.600
Okay.

00:11:03.120 --> 00:11:04.580
I'll take them down first.

00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:58.400
Wu Wei, Wu Wei.

00:12:16.600 --> 00:12:18.120
Hold on, Ziqi.

00:12:18.400 --> 00:12:18.920
Come on.

00:12:21.280 --> 00:12:22.000
Wu Wei.

00:12:22.760 --> 00:12:24.120
Lock the car doors first.

00:12:24.120 --> 00:12:25.920
The next shift will be here soon.

00:12:34.600 --> 00:12:35.860
Come on, get in the car.

00:12:39.360 --> 00:12:40.690
What were you thinking?

00:12:41.280 --> 00:12:42.600
This is a launch mission,

00:12:42.600 --> 00:12:43.480
not a drill.

00:12:43.480 --> 00:12:45.140
How could you leave your post?

00:12:45.360 --> 00:12:46.280
Are you crazy?

00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:48.560
There was a problem with the line voltage.

00:12:48.560 --> 00:12:50.360
I wanted to fix it before the mission.

00:12:50.360 --> 00:12:51.160
It was an emergency,

00:12:51.160 --> 00:12:52.290
so there was no time.

00:12:52.880 --> 00:12:54.200
No time?

00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:54.880
No time.

00:12:54.880 --> 00:12:57.080
What's the point of having these rules?

00:12:57.520 --> 00:12:58.450
Fine, whatever.

00:12:58.720 --> 00:13:00.180
What I say doesn't matter.

00:13:00.360 --> 00:13:01.960
I just feel sorry for you.

00:13:01.960 --> 00:13:02.920
To be exact,

00:13:03.360 --> 00:13:05.280
I feel sorry for Ying Ziqi.

00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:06.120
You know?

00:13:06.480 --> 00:13:07.600
Think about it.

00:13:35.240 --> 00:13:36.640
What's wrong with Wu Wei?

00:13:38.440 --> 00:13:40.640
How could he make such a rookie mistake?

00:13:44.920 --> 00:13:45.880
I'm sorry.

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:47.130
I let everyone down.

00:13:47.400 --> 00:13:48.530
It's not your fault.

00:13:49.120 --> 00:13:50.380
It's all because of me.

00:13:51.680 --> 00:13:53.410
Okay, go back and get some rest.

00:13:53.640 --> 00:13:55.560
Do a good job with the rest of the work.

00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:56.160
By the way,

00:13:56.400 --> 00:13:57.600
Lao Qin and Lao Gu

00:13:57.600 --> 00:13:58.930
asked you to go see them.

00:14:14.560 --> 00:14:15.240
Reporting.

00:14:17.640 --> 00:14:18.400
Come in.

00:14:30.480 --> 00:14:31.400
Let me ask you,

00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:33.680
why?

00:14:35.160 --> 00:14:35.720
I...

00:14:39.560 --> 00:14:41.690
Why did you make such a rookie mistake?

00:14:42.200 --> 00:14:44.040
I was rushing to check the circuits,

00:14:44.040 --> 00:14:46.040
afraid of delaying the measurement.

00:14:46.040 --> 00:14:47.160
In my rush, I...

00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:50.440
Mr. Qin, Mr. Gu.

00:14:51.440 --> 00:14:52.200
I know

00:14:52.760 --> 00:14:54.090
I violated discipline.

00:14:54.440 --> 00:14:55.120
But...

00:14:56.840 --> 00:14:58.480
I was the one who left without permission.

00:14:58.480 --> 00:15:00.040
Ying Ziqi had a fever.

00:15:00.320 --> 00:15:01.080
He didn't even know.

00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:01.960
And?

00:15:04.040 --> 00:15:04.720
So I think

00:15:04.720 --> 00:15:06.240
punishing Ying Ziqi with me

00:15:06.240 --> 00:15:06.960
is unfair.

00:15:07.640 --> 00:15:09.280
No, it was my fault.

00:15:09.280 --> 00:15:09.840
I shouldn't have... Ying Ziqi, shut up!

00:15:09.840 --> 00:15:11.000
Both of you, shut up.

00:15:16.120 --> 00:15:18.040
You are a team.

00:15:18.400 --> 00:15:19.040
It's a dual-post system.

00:15:19.040 --> 00:15:19.840
That's the discipline.

00:15:19.840 --> 00:15:21.760
If you still don't realize this,

00:15:21.920 --> 00:15:23.120
why are you even here?

00:15:29.080 --> 00:15:30.610
What did you tell me before?

00:15:34.320 --> 00:15:35.560
Didn't you say

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:36.640
that

00:15:37.400 --> 00:15:39.320
this was your promise to me?

00:15:39.840 --> 00:15:41.400
Is this the result you use

00:15:41.400 --> 00:15:42.440
to take over the baton?

00:15:42.440 --> 00:15:44.240
Take it back. I don't want it.

00:15:51.080 --> 00:15:51.680
Qin.

00:15:53.040 --> 00:15:54.680
You just recovered your health.

00:15:54.680 --> 00:15:56.280
Get out. All of you, get out!

00:15:57.400 --> 00:15:59.660
Think it over carefully when you go back.

00:16:10.280 --> 00:16:11.680
Go back and reflect on it.

00:16:16.160 --> 00:16:18.960
Your health comes first right now. Don't be angry.

00:16:25.680 --> 00:16:26.680
China Aerospace.

00:16:36.360 --> 00:16:37.820
If it wasn't handled then,

00:16:38.200 --> 00:16:39.160
our active telemetry and control stations

00:16:39.160 --> 00:16:40.890
would have lost their meaning.

00:16:41.600 --> 00:16:43.000
But this was my decision.

00:16:43.240 --> 00:16:44.840
I will take responsibility.

00:16:45.480 --> 00:16:47.540
It's me who got sick and burdened you.

00:16:49.080 --> 00:16:50.080
Otherwise,

00:16:50.080 --> 00:16:52.140
you wouldn't have to handle it alone.

00:16:52.160 --> 00:16:53.620
Let's not talk about this.

00:17:08.400 --> 00:17:10.859
Let's double-check this contingency plan.

00:17:15.880 --> 00:17:16.599
How are you feeling?

00:17:16.599 --> 00:17:17.880
Can you handle it?

00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:22.119
You look a little nervous.

00:17:22.119 --> 00:17:23.680
Stay calm.

00:17:24.599 --> 00:17:26.560
Save that for yourself.

00:17:27.800 --> 00:17:29.060
What, are you nervous?

00:17:29.760 --> 00:17:31.490
I'm not nervous. I'm very calm.

00:17:32.320 --> 00:17:33.600
I know you too well.

00:17:34.400 --> 00:17:37.240
You always ask me this on purpose at times like this.

00:17:37.240 --> 00:17:38.770
You're spreading anxiety,

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:39.640
you know?

00:17:39.880 --> 00:17:41.320
As the saying goes,

00:17:42.600 --> 00:17:43.880
by spreading anxiety,

00:17:43.880 --> 00:17:46.400
you can transform it, right?

00:17:46.560 --> 00:17:48.160
Transform yours.

00:17:48.400 --> 00:17:49.320
I don't need it.

00:17:51.760 --> 00:17:53.640
I will use all my luck in this life

00:17:54.240 --> 00:17:55.400
for this moment.

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:03.000
How about putting both of our luck

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:04.120
together?

00:18:13.840 --> 00:18:15.040
Everyone, get ready.

00:18:15.800 --> 00:18:18.200
Do a final check for the Hao-4 mission.

00:18:18.640 --> 00:18:19.400
This time,

00:18:19.880 --> 00:18:23.160
the flight control team has reduced the latitude deviation of the landing point

00:18:23.160 --> 00:18:25.360
to one hundred-thousandth of a degree,

00:18:25.400 --> 00:18:27.400
increasing the accuracy tenfold.

00:18:28.400 --> 00:18:29.800
It is unprecedented.

00:18:30.280 --> 00:18:32.880
This is the most difficult precision control.

00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:35.600
Thank you for your hard work.

00:18:41.400 --> 00:18:42.120
Comrades,

00:18:44.560 --> 00:18:46.080
since the dawn of humanity,

00:18:46.080 --> 00:18:47.760
we have never seen this.

00:18:47.760 --> 00:18:49.320
The far side of the moon.

00:18:49.720 --> 00:18:51.880
This is the first time

00:18:52.200 --> 00:18:54.320
a human creation has appeared on the far side.

00:18:54.320 --> 00:18:55.380
We must understand

00:18:55.840 --> 00:18:57.600
that what we are establishing today

00:18:57.600 --> 00:19:01.280
is a monument in the history of human spaceflight.

00:19:01.680 --> 00:19:02.520
I hope

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:05.130
we can work together

00:19:06.360 --> 00:19:07.690
to take this final step.

00:19:26.360 --> 00:19:27.120
Report.

00:19:27.480 --> 00:19:28.760
The moon has left its orbit

00:19:28.760 --> 00:19:30.690
and is going to collide with Earth.

00:19:31.520 --> 00:19:34.050
It's going to collide. Is anyone responding?

00:19:34.200 --> 00:19:36.520
Hello? Hello?

00:19:37.080 --> 00:19:38.120
The moon has left its orbit

00:19:38.120 --> 00:19:40.050
and is going to collide with Earth.

00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:42.610
It's going to collide! Is anyone responding?

00:21:04.840 --> 00:21:07.080
Mr. Qin, Mr. Gu.

00:21:08.200 --> 00:21:10.880
This letter is not a sudden impulse.

00:21:12.240 --> 00:21:13.320
Since I came back,

00:21:13.640 --> 00:21:14.520
I have been thinking about

00:21:14.520 --> 00:21:16.240
what you two said to me.

00:21:17.080 --> 00:21:19.480
I have also been reflecting on my mistakes.

00:21:19.840 --> 00:21:21.100
Thinking about it now,

00:21:21.840 --> 00:21:22.600
Perhaps from the very beginning,

00:21:22.600 --> 00:21:24.360
I never cared about discipline

00:21:25.040 --> 00:21:26.120
or rules.

00:21:28.720 --> 00:21:29.880
Since I came here,

00:21:30.320 --> 00:21:33.200
from trying my best to stay in the flight control team at first

00:21:33.200 --> 00:21:35.800
to desperately wanting to prove myself later.

00:21:35.880 --> 00:21:36.920
Along the way,

00:21:37.440 --> 00:21:38.400
many teachers

00:21:38.720 --> 00:21:40.520
and friends have criticized me.

00:21:41.880 --> 00:21:42.680
But actually,

00:21:43.680 --> 00:21:45.610
I have never faced these problems.

00:21:49.280 --> 00:21:50.440
Now I finally understand

00:21:50.440 --> 00:21:52.100
how serious my mistakes were,

00:21:52.680 --> 00:21:53.920
how unforgivable,

00:21:54.280 --> 00:21:55.610
and how wrong they were.

00:21:56.720 --> 00:21:57.560
I am sorry.

00:21:58.440 --> 00:21:59.600
This time,

00:21:59.600 --> 00:22:00.760
I let you down.

00:22:03.960 --> 00:22:06.080
Ying Ziqi and I watched Yutu No. 2

00:22:06.520 --> 00:22:08.380
succeed in its tests step by step.

00:22:09.520 --> 00:22:11.250
Just like everyone else feels,

00:22:12.080 --> 00:22:13.760
it's like a child to all of us.

00:22:21.560 --> 00:22:23.890
I am willing to bear all the consequences.

00:22:24.440 --> 00:22:26.480
I can leave the flight control center

00:22:26.480 --> 00:22:28.540
or transfer to any other department.

00:22:29.560 --> 00:22:30.240
But...

00:22:31.800 --> 00:22:33.660
But please give Ying Ziqi a chance

00:22:34.440 --> 00:22:36.500
to complete the remaining missions.

00:22:37.360 --> 00:22:40.120
Please consider my request.

00:22:41.240 --> 00:22:41.920
Wu Wei.

00:22:43.000 --> 00:22:44.880
Are you clear on the follow-up process?

00:22:44.880 --> 00:22:45.960
You must pay attention to the details.

00:22:45.960 --> 00:22:47.490
Ensure nothing goes wrong.

00:22:56.800 --> 00:22:57.480
Xiao Qu.

00:22:58.960 --> 00:22:59.690
Understood.

00:23:00.600 --> 00:23:01.530
Get back to work.

00:23:41.040 --> 00:23:42.840
Packing up? Where are you going?

00:23:43.880 --> 00:23:46.210
Something came up at home. I'm going back.

00:23:54.320 --> 00:23:55.650
Transfer application.

00:23:58.520 --> 00:23:59.920
Why are you writing this?

00:24:46.240 --> 00:24:46.920
Wu Wei.

00:24:48.760 --> 00:24:51.960
Have you forgotten the dream you've had since childhood?

00:24:53.560 --> 00:24:55.040
The words you said to the three of us before joining,

00:24:55.040 --> 00:24:56.320
have you forgotten them too?

00:24:56.320 --> 00:24:57.360
The three of us are still holding on,

00:24:57.360 --> 00:24:58.640
and only you have given up.

00:24:58.640 --> 00:25:00.120
The way you are now

00:25:00.240 --> 00:25:02.040
really makes me look down on you.

00:25:02.040 --> 00:25:03.200
Are you done?

00:25:06.040 --> 00:25:07.300
Do you feel better now?

00:25:08.320 --> 00:25:09.400
If you do, get out.

00:25:40.120 --> 00:25:40.840
Now I will

00:25:40.840 --> 00:25:42.570
read out the penalty decision.

00:25:44.240 --> 00:25:47.170
During the Gaoshan-2 tracking and control mission,

00:25:47.360 --> 00:25:49.240
Wu Wei and Ying Ziqi

00:25:49.240 --> 00:25:50.840
violated the flight control discipline

00:25:50.840 --> 00:25:52.000
by leaving their posts without permission.

00:25:52.000 --> 00:25:54.840
The flight control center imposes the following penalty on them:

00:25:54.840 --> 00:25:55.920
Wu Wei and Ying Ziqi

00:25:55.920 --> 00:25:57.440
are each given a warning,

00:25:58.400 --> 00:26:00.480
transferred out of the Haoyue-4 mission,

00:26:00.480 --> 00:26:02.200
and reassigned to the daily monitoring team

00:26:02.200 --> 00:26:04.130
to observe their future behavior.

00:27:28.680 --> 00:27:30.400
Hao-4 is about to perform an Earth-Moon orbital maneuver.

00:27:30.400 --> 00:27:31.930
Let's go watch it together.

00:27:34.160 --> 00:27:34.960
I'm not going.

00:28:03.360 --> 00:28:04.220
Where is Wu Wei?

00:28:06.240 --> 00:28:08.100
I asked him, but he wouldn't come.

00:28:09.440 --> 00:28:10.700
Is Wei still like that?

00:28:11.840 --> 00:28:12.600
Jia.

00:28:13.080 --> 00:28:14.080
Everyone's here.

00:28:17.800 --> 00:28:20.080
Here are your flight tickets to Jiuquan.

00:28:22.560 --> 00:28:23.960
After the mission is over,

00:28:23.960 --> 00:28:25.360
have a good talk with him.

00:28:27.080 --> 00:28:27.680
Okay.

00:28:28.840 --> 00:28:29.800
It's almost time.

00:28:29.800 --> 00:28:31.130
You should go get ready.

00:28:31.520 --> 00:28:33.050
Good luck with the mission.

00:28:34.160 --> 00:28:34.720
Okay.

00:28:35.400 --> 00:28:36.080
Let's go.

00:29:38.600 --> 00:29:39.320
This is...

00:30:04.000 --> 00:30:05.480
Sir, take a rest.

00:30:05.480 --> 00:30:06.680
We'll wipe it for you.

00:30:06.680 --> 00:30:08.520
I'm not tired. I'm used to it.

00:30:10.560 --> 00:30:12.290
Are you aerospace workers too?

00:30:12.640 --> 00:30:13.240
Yes.

00:30:14.280 --> 00:30:15.340
Which department?

00:30:15.840 --> 00:30:17.370
We are from flight control.

00:30:18.120 --> 00:30:19.520
I'm from the launch site.

00:30:21.200 --> 00:30:22.520
Have you

00:30:22.520 --> 00:30:23.840
been in Jiuquan all along?

00:30:23.840 --> 00:30:25.240
I retired a long time ago.

00:30:25.440 --> 00:30:26.920
My roots are here.

00:30:27.560 --> 00:30:28.280
So

00:30:28.920 --> 00:30:29.920
I just stay here,

00:30:30.320 --> 00:30:32.980
keeping my old colleagues and buddies company.

00:30:33.920 --> 00:30:34.600
Young men,

00:30:35.360 --> 00:30:37.200
don't you have a mission recently?

00:30:37.200 --> 00:30:38.440
What brings you here?

00:30:39.240 --> 00:30:40.360
We made a mistake

00:30:41.560 --> 00:30:42.420
on our mission.

00:30:43.120 --> 00:30:43.840
So...

00:30:44.560 --> 00:30:46.280
When I was your age,

00:30:46.640 --> 00:30:48.170
I had just started working.

00:30:48.440 --> 00:30:50.570
I was also reckless when doing things.

00:30:53.920 --> 00:30:55.080
This is Xiao Liu.

00:30:55.200 --> 00:30:57.840
He came to Jiuquan in the same batch as us.

00:30:58.240 --> 00:30:59.760
He was the youngest

00:30:59.960 --> 00:31:01.890
and had the hardest time adapting.

00:31:01.920 --> 00:31:03.920
How could those days compare to now?

00:31:04.120 --> 00:31:05.850
Now there's an aerospace city,

00:31:06.440 --> 00:31:08.440
and we've done so many major missions.

00:31:08.440 --> 00:31:10.160
It's so well-equipped.

00:31:10.440 --> 00:31:11.440
Back then,

00:31:12.080 --> 00:31:14.610
we had nothing but sandstorms and blizzards.

00:31:15.720 --> 00:31:17.080
But Xiao Liu liked it.

00:31:17.840 --> 00:31:20.200
He liked winter, liked the snow,

00:31:21.560 --> 00:31:23.840
and liked to draw in a little notebook.

00:31:24.440 --> 00:31:25.920
Well, southerners

00:31:26.240 --> 00:31:27.370
care about rituals.

00:31:28.080 --> 00:31:29.440
He drew almost

00:31:29.720 --> 00:31:31.200
all the scenery here.

00:31:31.760 --> 00:31:32.960
He had planned that

00:31:33.920 --> 00:31:35.380
after he left the mission,

00:31:37.240 --> 00:31:38.570
and could communicate,

00:31:39.200 --> 00:31:40.440
he would send this notebook

00:31:40.440 --> 00:31:41.920
back home to his partner,

00:31:42.360 --> 00:31:45.160
saving it for telling stories and bragging later.

00:31:47.560 --> 00:31:48.400
What a pity.

00:31:49.040 --> 00:31:51.770
He always carried that little notebook with him.

00:31:53.040 --> 00:31:54.700
Later, there was an accident,

00:31:55.320 --> 00:31:56.850
and he sacrificed himself.

00:31:57.120 --> 00:32:00.240
That little notebook was gone with him.

00:32:01.200 --> 00:32:02.730
The bragging he wanted to do

00:32:03.360 --> 00:32:04.200
is also gone.

00:32:05.440 --> 00:32:07.700
The reason I'm telling you about Xiaoliu

00:32:07.880 --> 00:32:10.080
is because he also made mistakes before

00:32:10.320 --> 00:32:11.580
and started from zero.

00:32:11.600 --> 00:32:12.640
But in the end,

00:32:13.120 --> 00:32:14.800
he also made great contributions.

00:32:14.800 --> 00:32:15.600
Young man,

00:32:16.440 --> 00:32:17.240
I don't know

00:32:17.240 --> 00:32:19.320
what exactly happened to you guys.

00:32:19.800 --> 00:32:21.640
But I think the logic

00:32:22.720 --> 00:32:24.380
is like a scientific theorem.

00:32:24.880 --> 00:32:26.440
If you plug in certain parameters,

00:32:26.440 --> 00:32:28.170
it's universally applicable.

00:32:29.040 --> 00:32:29.920
Am I right?

00:32:32.680 --> 00:32:34.480
You must have been through a lot.

00:32:35.080 --> 00:32:36.720
What? You want to hear a story?

00:32:36.720 --> 00:32:37.440
All right.

00:32:38.320 --> 00:32:39.850
Over there, my team leader,

00:32:39.920 --> 00:32:41.440
my master, my apprentice,

00:32:41.440 --> 00:32:42.760
they are all here.

00:32:43.120 --> 00:32:43.800
Let's go.

00:32:43.920 --> 00:32:45.850
I'll do some bragging for them too.

00:32:46.720 --> 00:32:47.250
Let's go.

00:32:59.280 --> 00:33:00.440
In 1956,

00:33:02.080 --> 00:33:03.440
on October 8th,

00:33:04.840 --> 00:33:06.560
the Fifth Academy of the Ministry of National Defense was established.

00:33:06.560 --> 00:33:09.290
This is the starting point of China's aerospace.

00:33:13.320 --> 00:33:15.380
Do you know what my starting point is?

00:33:27.920 --> 00:33:30.180
Ever since you told me when we were little

00:33:30.720 --> 00:33:32.520
that you sent a signal to aliens,

00:33:36.080 --> 00:33:37.240
I've always felt

00:33:38.280 --> 00:33:39.200
that maybe one day

00:33:39.200 --> 00:33:41.260
we'll actually receive their reply.

00:33:44.160 --> 00:33:45.690
This broken radio of yours,

00:33:46.800 --> 00:33:50.060
I don't know how many times I've repaired it over the years.

00:34:00.920 --> 00:34:02.250
Do you still believe it?

00:34:05.840 --> 00:34:06.570
I believe it.

00:34:07.640 --> 00:34:08.639
Of course I do.

00:34:09.280 --> 00:34:11.340
They are right there, waiting for us.

00:34:12.400 --> 00:34:13.400
Sooner or later,

00:34:13.400 --> 00:34:15.080
we will go to their planet.

00:34:16.159 --> 00:34:17.120
So,

00:34:17.639 --> 00:34:19.040
if you hadn't tricked me

00:34:19.040 --> 00:34:21.600
into entering that rocket competition when we were kids,

00:34:21.600 --> 00:34:22.679
in my whole life,

00:34:22.679 --> 00:34:25.120
I would never have crossed paths with aerospace.

00:34:25.120 --> 00:34:26.980
I wouldn't even look up at the sky.

00:34:29.560 --> 00:34:31.219
When my mom first passed away,

00:34:33.920 --> 00:34:35.360
I researched every day.

00:34:37.679 --> 00:34:39.540
I wanted to invent a time machine.

00:34:40.880 --> 00:34:42.080
I wanted

00:34:42.080 --> 00:34:43.760
to rewrite the timeline.

00:34:45.800 --> 00:34:48.000
Later, when I went to junior high school

00:34:48.280 --> 00:34:51.840
and learned the law of conservation of energy and the laws of thermodynamics,

00:34:51.840 --> 00:34:52.719
I knew

00:34:53.920 --> 00:34:55.199
it was all in vain.

00:34:57.600 --> 00:34:58.400
Our universe

00:34:58.400 --> 00:35:00.460
is an entropy-increasing universe.

00:35:01.120 --> 00:35:03.720
It determines the irreversible arrow of time.

00:35:04.400 --> 00:35:05.440
So I believe

00:35:06.920 --> 00:35:08.560
that all unfulfilled wishes

00:35:09.680 --> 00:35:12.340
are alternative arrangements of the timeline.

00:35:20.040 --> 00:35:20.680
Right.

00:35:23.240 --> 00:35:24.770
The past cannot be changed.

00:35:25.880 --> 00:35:27.280
We can only move forward.

00:35:28.920 --> 00:35:30.960
I believe this is the ultimate driving force for humanity

00:35:30.960 --> 00:35:32.960
to seek answers about the universe.

00:35:37.920 --> 00:35:38.640
Wu Wei.

00:35:40.240 --> 00:35:42.040
You used to pull us forward

00:35:42.440 --> 00:35:43.440
and encourage us.

00:35:44.640 --> 00:35:47.170
You can't be the first one to give up this time.

00:35:50.200 --> 00:35:51.040
I understand.

00:35:52.600 --> 00:35:55.920
Generations of predecessors' efforts and sacrifices

00:35:56.720 --> 00:35:59.250
have made China's aerospace what it is today.

00:35:59.440 --> 00:36:01.120
None of them gave up easily.

00:36:02.080 --> 00:36:03.740
What right do I have to give up?

00:36:05.960 --> 00:36:06.960
After I go back,

00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:09.500
I'll delete my account

00:36:10.280 --> 00:36:11.680
and start all over again.

00:36:12.680 --> 00:36:13.840
Keep your word.

00:36:14.680 --> 00:36:15.320
I will.

00:36:20.280 --> 00:36:21.960
The lunar landing is about to begin.

00:36:21.960 --> 00:36:22.960
Trust the rabbit.

00:36:33.000 --> 00:36:34.960
Haoyue 4 has navigated to

00:36:34.960 --> 00:36:37.720
the perilune 15 kilometers above the far side of the moon.

00:36:37.720 --> 00:36:39.450
7,500-newton engine started.

00:36:39.800 --> 00:36:41.200
Powered descent begins.

00:36:48.080 --> 00:36:49.560
Hope it lands safely.

00:36:53.440 --> 00:36:54.960
Entering the main deceleration phase.

00:36:54.960 --> 00:36:56.220
Everything is normal.

00:37:03.280 --> 00:37:06.010
Fast adjustment phase entering approach phase.

00:37:06.840 --> 00:37:08.080
Everything is normal.

00:37:08.080 --> 00:37:10.610
Optical sensor data transmission is normal.

00:37:15.800 --> 00:37:17.560
The terrain near the landing site is flat.

00:37:17.560 --> 00:37:18.720
Obstacle avoidance sensor is working normally.

00:37:18.720 --> 00:37:19.360
Copy.

00:37:19.840 --> 00:37:21.520
Entering hover obstacle avoidance phase.

00:37:21.520 --> 00:37:22.780
Everything is normal.

00:37:48.640 --> 00:37:50.040
Confirm landing status.

00:37:56.320 --> 00:37:58.720
The lander's lunar landing attitude is normal.

00:37:58.720 --> 00:38:00.440
Solar arrays deployed normally.

00:38:00.440 --> 00:38:02.440
Lander optical imaging is normal.

00:38:02.440 --> 00:38:04.000
Charging baseline is normal.

00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:06.060
Orbit control accurately shut down.

00:38:06.400 --> 00:38:09.040
Attitude control engine accurately shut down.

00:38:09.040 --> 00:38:10.320
Report lunar landing coordinates.

00:38:10.320 --> 00:38:12.600
Based on the analysis of the returned high-compression ratio images,

00:38:12.600 --> 00:38:14.120
the Haoyue-4 lander's

00:38:14.320 --> 00:38:15.840
preliminary landing position

00:38:15.840 --> 00:38:16.770
coordinates are

00:38:16.800 --> 00:38:19.040
177°60' East Longitude,

00:38:19.320 --> 00:38:21.600
45°44' South Latitude.

00:38:22.600 --> 00:38:23.530
Ideal position.

00:38:24.880 --> 00:38:25.560
Copy.

00:38:39.320 --> 00:38:40.280
It's too quiet.

00:38:41.200 --> 00:38:42.240
You can cheer now.

00:38:42.240 --> 00:38:43.100
It's a success.

00:39:13.640 --> 00:39:16.040
We didn't eat the herbal jelly for nothing.

00:39:16.040 --> 00:39:17.800
And we didn't argue for nothing.

00:39:17.800 --> 00:39:19.400
Alright, you idiot.

00:39:19.760 --> 00:39:21.020
Sister Nan, thank you.

00:39:21.400 --> 00:39:23.080
Come on, don't be cheesy.

00:39:23.080 --> 00:39:24.120
I'm not.

00:39:24.600 --> 00:39:26.600
I... I really mean it.

00:39:27.080 --> 00:39:28.400
Thank you for scolding me, pushing me,

00:39:28.400 --> 00:39:29.730
and pulling me forward.

00:39:29.800 --> 00:39:31.120
It's all worth it now.

00:39:31.640 --> 00:39:33.240
With this landing precision,

00:39:33.240 --> 00:39:34.840
and the control technology.

00:39:34.920 --> 00:39:37.180
China's aerospace crushes everything.

00:39:37.520 --> 00:39:38.160
Alright.

00:39:45.240 --> 00:39:46.240
Latest news.

00:39:46.240 --> 00:39:47.760
The Haoyue-4 probe

00:39:47.760 --> 00:39:49.960
has successfully landed on the far side of the moon.

00:39:49.960 --> 00:39:52.480
This mission marks the realization of a human probe.

00:39:52.480 --> 00:39:54.080
Landing on the moon is just the first step.

00:39:54.080 --> 00:39:55.600
Whether the rabbit can come out smoothly

00:39:55.600 --> 00:39:57.200
is the most important thing.

00:39:57.880 --> 00:39:58.560
Yes.

00:39:59.320 --> 00:40:00.920
But judging from the images,

00:40:01.040 --> 00:40:02.280
the place where the rabbit got off,

00:40:02.280 --> 00:40:04.680
the terrain and geomorphology are relatively flat.

00:40:04.680 --> 00:40:05.320
Next,

00:40:05.320 --> 00:40:08.280
we will just wait for the results of the terrain data processing.

00:40:08.280 --> 00:40:09.200
Each subsystem,

00:40:09.200 --> 00:40:11.000
we have also repeatedly tested.

00:40:11.040 --> 00:40:13.000
Even if the situation on the far side of the moon is more complex,

00:40:13.000 --> 00:40:14.520
the rabbit can handle it.

00:40:15.560 --> 00:40:16.680
It's up to Xu Xu.

00:40:27.360 --> 00:40:28.890
Why are they sleeping here?

00:40:33.080 --> 00:40:34.320
Aren't they afraid of catching a cold?

00:40:34.320 --> 00:40:35.440
Let them sleep.

00:40:36.160 --> 00:40:38.000
They haven't closed their eyes for days.

00:40:38.000 --> 00:40:39.600
They'll be busy again later.

00:40:40.080 --> 00:40:41.560
Look at Caibao's pose.

00:40:41.800 --> 00:40:43.260
How can he sleep like that?

00:40:57.880 --> 00:40:59.140
Everyone, take a break

00:40:59.600 --> 00:41:00.400
and get ready.

00:41:00.760 --> 00:41:01.320
Yes.

00:41:04.320 --> 00:41:06.120
It's up to you next.

00:41:08.440 --> 00:41:09.560
I am ready.

00:41:15.560 --> 00:41:17.620
Report the status of all subsystems.

00:41:26.520 --> 00:41:28.080
Relay link is normal.

00:41:28.280 --> 00:41:30.160
TT&C and data transmission are normal.

00:41:30.160 --> 00:41:32.640
Begin rover transfer.

00:41:35.880 --> 00:41:37.680
Rover deploying solar panels

00:41:37.840 --> 00:41:39.040
and raising the mast.

00:41:42.280 --> 00:41:43.240
Prepare to execute

00:41:43.240 --> 00:41:46.240
the subsequent procedures for Yutu's lunar release.

00:41:48.080 --> 00:41:50.340
Transfer mechanism unlocked normally.

00:41:53.280 --> 00:41:54.340
Transfer started.

00:42:03.600 --> 00:42:06.000
Report the current status of all stations.

00:42:06.120 --> 00:42:07.920
Rover transferred in position.

00:42:08.480 --> 00:42:09.740
Yutu status is normal.

00:42:25.760 --> 00:42:27.960
The last leg of a journey is the hardest.

00:42:30.640 --> 00:42:31.560
I'm just worried.

00:42:31.560 --> 00:42:33.240
The situation on the far side of the moon is complex.

00:42:33.240 --> 00:42:34.240
After all,

00:42:35.040 --> 00:42:36.440
none of us have ever been there.

00:42:36.440 --> 00:42:37.770
Driving the Yutu rover.

00:42:38.880 --> 00:42:40.720
Communication with the relay satellite

00:42:40.720 --> 00:42:42.050
is extremely critical.

00:42:43.800 --> 00:42:46.400
Hopefully, our preparations are sufficient.

00:42:47.680 --> 00:42:48.880
We should trust them.

00:43:00.760 --> 00:43:03.640
The spacecraft names and related missions in this drama are fictionalized.

